Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs` to hook platform-native callbacks directly:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when activity loses focus
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when activity is no longer visible
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // Runs when app enters background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key things to know:**

- **Android `OnPause`** maps to the cross-platform `Deactivated` event (lost focus, may still be visible). **`OnStop`** maps to `Stopped` (fully backgrounded).
- **iOS `DidEnterBackground`** maps to `Stopped`.
- Keep handlers **fast** — Android enforces a ~5s ANR timeout, iOS has limited background time.
- On Android, the **back button can skip `OnStop`** and go straight to `OnDestroy`, so also handle `OnDestroy` if you're saving critical state.

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback signatures, you can use the `Window.Stopped` event instead — it fires on all platforms:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* save state here */ };
    return window;
}
```
